His pavilion project as a temporary construction had been exhibited after the universal exhibition in the Garden Switzerland at the Southern Vienna Station, was transformed, and in 1962 a 20th century museum opened -
But the building was neither physically nor technically suitable for a museum - no walls to hang the works of art, so not a good environment.
However, it has been used so long, until contemporary art receives a new building in Vienna.
Since 2001, the building has been empty and has become increasingly unleashed.
Now architect Adolf Krischanitz transformed the Pavilion, now he bears the name of "Maison of the 21st Century" and will be used in the future as a museum for contemporary art.
Tuesday evening the Belvédère museum opened, to which the house belongs, the first exhibition - a lucky hit at any point of view.
