Strict surveillance, small budget
For the realization, Krischanitz was therefore the ideal interpreter.
Not only because he had sensitively transformed and expanded Joseph Olbracht's secession and won the contest, but because he had studied at the Technical University of Vienna and for him the pavilion was "an extremely important" place where he had seen "practically every weekend" exhibitions.
He knew the original project, and he knew the problems of the building, which lost generosity and lightness as a result of his movement to Vienna and his change in use.
In the current transformations there were big problems: the building was “a energy buffer,” says Krischanitz.
The window profiles of glass facades were changed, glass fiber-reinforced insulating glass was laid and the roof was replaced by a particular safety glass.
Thermal bridges were reinforced or replaced, and asbestos-filled coatings were rehabilitated.
Two ground floors have made space for the new operation, a light panel sealed between the house and the road ensures lighting, a bridge leads to the entrance - this is almost a new construction, but always the lightweight Schwanzer Pavilion.
