If the signals that the pavement were solved, it would no longer be necessary to repair about 200 thousand cracks every rain season in the Metropolitan Zone of Valle de México, warns Rafael Herrera Nájera, researcher at UNAM’s Chemistry Faculty (FQ), who assured that if the construction and maintenance process of the pavement is completely reduced or the cases.
