The arrangement adopted by the Austrian government approaches the German model, since Germany was the first European country to adopt such a "rule".
By 2017, the structural public deficit will have to decrease by 0.75% each year of the Gross Domestic Product (GDP) and, starting in 2017, the federal government’s structural public deficit will not have to exceed 0.35% each year of the GDP, while regional states and municipalities will have to make budgets at a balance.
